<Section xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation" xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml" FontFamily="Arial" FontSize="10"> 
	<Table Margin="20,20,20,0" BorderBrush="Black" BorderThickness="2">
		<Table.Resources>
			<Style TargetType="{x:Type TableCell}">	
				<Setter Property="Padding" Value="4,4,4,4" />	
			</Style>
			<Style TargetType="{x:Type Paragraph}">
				<Setter Property="Margin" Value="0" />
			</Style>
		</Table.Resources>
    <Table.Columns>
		<TableColumn Width="300" />
    </Table.Columns>
		<TableRowGroup>
			<TableRow Background="White">
				 <TableCell>
					<Paragraph>
						<Floater Background="Red" Padding="0" Margin="3" HorizontalAlignment="Left" Width="75">
							<Paragraph FontSize="14">This is a Floater in a TableCell. This is a Floater in a TableCell. This is a Floater in a TableCell. This is a Floater in a TableCell. END</Paragraph>
						</Floater>
						<Bold Foreground="Blue">Row 1</Bold> Nearly all reptiles have three-chambered hearts; the exceptions are crocodilians, which have four-chambered hearts.
					</Paragraph>
				</TableCell>
			</TableRow>
			<TableRow Background="White">
				 <TableCell>
					<Paragraph ClearFloaters="Both">
						<Bold Foreground="Blue">Row 2</Bold> Nearly all reptiles have three-chambered hearts; the exceptions are crocodilians, which have four-chambered hearts.
					</Paragraph>
				</TableCell>
			</TableRow>	
		</TableRowGroup>
	</Table>
</Section>
